Dialogue: 4,0:20:50.80,0:20:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nice work out there.
Dialogue: 4,0:20:52.32,0:20:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Producer. Nice work yourself.
Dialogue: 4,0:20:55.49,0:20:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It was a great show.
Dialogue: 4,0:20:57.18,0:21:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}How did it feel to see what \Nit's like to be an idol again?
Dialogue: 4,0:21:00.24,0:21:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's see.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:01.93,0:21:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Singing my lungs out on stage, \Nlistening to the screaming fans...
Dialogue: 4,0:21:06.42,0:21:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, it might \Nhave been pretty fun.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:10.45,0:21:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this isn't the place I belong.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:14.35,0:21:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's their job to bathe \Nin the light and sparkle.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:17.70,0:21:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My job is to make them \Nsparkle even more.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:22.38,0:21:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That became very clear to me. {ALT: I found that out for sure/I most definitely learned that. All awkward}
Dialogue: 4,0:21:25.52,0:21:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:27.56,0:21:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or something like that. \NYou never know what'll happen.
Dialogue: 4,0:21:31.74,0:21:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I suddenly decide, "I can't forget how it feels to be on stage.{if you think this looks retarded without a quote on the end or because of the starting quote at the next line, send a complaint to the Chicago Manual of Style for doing it like this and to kusion and TruePsyche for insisting to follow it}
Dialogue: 4,0:21:35.12,0:21:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm gonna make a \Ncomeback as an idol!"
